---
import PageLayout from "../layouts/PageLayout.astro";
---

<PageLayout
title="About"
description="Lookout West is an independent publication on the economics of the American West."
eyebrow="About"
intro="Lookout West is an independent publication on the economics of the American West."
prose={false}
contentWidth="wide"

>

  <div class="about-page">
    <section class="about-hero">
      <div class="about-hero__content">
        <p class="about-hero__label">About Lookout West</p>
        <h2 class="about-hero__title">
          The West is changing because its systems are changing.
        </h2>
        <p class="about-hero__deck">
          Water, land, power, housing, labor, and growth do not move separately for long.
          Lookout West follows those connections.
        </p>
        <p class="about-hero__note">
          The goal is to make the economics of the American West clearer without turning
          the region into a slogan, a dashboard, or a pile of disconnected trend stories.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

<section class="about-section">
  <div class="about-section__header">
    <p class="about-section__label">Why it exists</p>
    <h2 class="about-section__title">
      A lot of Western coverage is either too thin or too hard to use.
    </h2>
    <p class="about-section__description">
      The region is full of serious economic questions: who can afford to live where,
      how water gets allocated, where power demand is going, what growth does to local
      institutions, and how physical constraint shapes opportunity.
    </p>
    <p class="about-section__description">
      Those questions need more than quick commentary. They also need writing that
      normal busy people can actually read. Lookout West is built for that middle ground:
      rigorous enough to be useful, clear enough to stay with.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="about-section">
  <div class="about-section__header">
    <p class="about-section__label">How the work is handled</p>
    <h2 class="about-section__title">
      Start with the real constraint. Explain the mechanism. Keep the page readable.
    </h2>
    <p class="about-section__description">
      The publication comes first. Essays, research notes, charts, and visual explanation
      are the core product. Advisory work grows from that base; it should never pull the
      site away from the reading experience.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="about-grid">
    <article class="about-card">
      <h3>Follow the system</h3>
      <p>
        The useful story is usually not one variable. It is how water, land, housing,
        energy, labor, and public capacity press against each other.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="about-card">
      <h3>Use plain structure</h3>
      <p>
        Good analysis should not require a decoder ring. The work should be sharp,
        sourced, and written in a way that helps the reader keep moving.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="about-card">
      <h3>Show what helps</h3>
      <p>
        Charts, maps, and diagrams belong when they clarify the argument. They do not
        belong just because a page needs decoration.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="about-section">
  <div class="about-section__header">
    <p class="about-section__label">Coverage</p>
    <h2 class="about-section__title">
      The scope is narrow on purpose.
    </h2>
    <p class="about-section__description">
      Lookout West focuses on the recurring pressures that explain how the region works
      and where it is heading.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="coverage-grid">
    <article class="coverage-card">
      <h3>Land</h3>
      <p>Geography, ownership, development pressure, and physical constraint.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="coverage-card">
      <h3>Water</h3>
      <p>Scarcity, allocation, governance, infrastructure, pricing, and risk.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="coverage-card">
      <h3>Energy</h3>
      <p>Power demand, generation, transmission, resources, and industrial change.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="coverage-card">
      <h3>Housing</h3>
      <p>Costs, supply, migration, household strain, and local growth politics.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="coverage-card">
      <h3>Labor</h3>
      <p>Workforce shifts, wages, sector change, local adjustment, and opportunity.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="coverage-card">
      <h3>Growth</h3>
      <p>Infrastructure, institutions, demographics, and long-run regional change.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="about-section about-section--split">
  <div class="about-section__header">
    <p class="about-section__label">Editor</p>
    <h2 class="about-section__title">Edited by Henry Rawlings.</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="about-section__body">
    <p>
      My background is in economics, macroeconomic analysis, and institutional research.
      Lookout West is where I apply that lens to the region I care most about.
    </p>
    <p>
      I am interested in the parts of the West that do not fit neatly into national
      talking points: water systems, power demand, housing pressure, land constraint,
      labor adjustment, and the local institutions that have to make real decisions
      under pressure.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="about-section">
  <div class="about-section__header">
    <p class="about-section__label">Advisory work</p>
    <h2 class="about-section__title">
      Advisory work is available when there is a real question behind it.
    </h2>
    <p class="about-section__description">
      Lookout West can support briefings, custom research, market and regional analysis,
      and speaking for institutions that need a clearer view of the American West.
    </p>
    <p class="about-section__description">
      The right inquiry usually starts with something specific: a place, a sector, a
      decision, a board discussion, a public issue, or an audience that needs a better
      framework.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="about-cta">
  <p class="about-cta__label">Next steps</p>
  <h2 class="about-cta__title">
    Start with the research. Subscribe if you want the next piece. Reach out when there is a concrete question.
  </h2>

  <div class="about-cta__actions">
    <a class="button button--primary" href="/research">Read the research</a>
    <button class="button" type="button" data-subscribe-open>
      Subscribe
    </button>
    <a class="button" href="/contact">Start an inquiry</a>
  </div>
</section>

  </div>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-7);
  }

  .about-section {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-5);
  }

  .about-section + .about-section {
    padding-top: var(--space-5);
    border-top: var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .about-hero,
  .about-card,
  .coverage-card,
  .about-cta {
    padding: var(--space-5);
    border: var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.52);
  }

  .about-hero {
    width: min(100%, 68rem);
  }

  .about-cta {
    width: min(100%, 68rem);
    padding: var(--space-6);
  }

  .about-hero__content {
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  .about-section__header {
    max-width: 44rem;
  }

  .about-section__body {
    max-width: 42rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: var(--step-0);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .about-section__body p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .about-section__body p + p {
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about-hero__label,
  .about-section__label,
  .about-cta__label {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .about-hero__title {
    margin: var(--space-2) 0 0;
    max-width: 18ch;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.48rem, 1.9vw, 1.86rem);
    line-height: 1.08;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  .about-hero__deck,
  .about-hero__note {
    max-width: 40rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: var(--step-0);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .about-hero__deck {
    margin: var(--space-4) 0 0;
  }

  .about-hero__note {
    margin: var(--space-3) 0 0;
  }

  .about-section__description {
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    max-width: 44rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: var(--step-0);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .about-section__description + .about-section__description {
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
  }

  .about-section__title,
  .about-cta__title {
    margin: var(--space-2) 0 0;
    max-width: 27ch;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.26rem, 1.55vw, 1.52rem);
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  .about-grid,
  .coverage-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about-card,
  .coverage-card {
    display: grid;
    align-content: start;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .about-card h3,
  .coverage-card h3 {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(0.98rem, 1.02vw, 1.1rem);
    line-height: 1.12;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  .about-card p,
  .coverage-card p {
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 31ch;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .about-cta__actions {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    margin-top: var(--space-5);
  }

  @media (min-width: 68rem) {
    .about-grid,
    .coverage-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }

    .about-section--split {
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.8fr) minmax(0, 1.2fr);
      align-items: start;
      column-gap: var(--space-7);
    }

    .about-section--split .about-section__header {
      max-width: 28rem;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 56rem) {
    .about-page {
      gap: var(--space-6);
    }

    .about-section + .about-section {
      padding-top: var(--space-4);
    }

    .about-hero,
    .about-card,
    .coverage-card,
    .about-cta {
      border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    }

    .about-hero__deck,
    .about-hero__note,
    .about-section__description,
    .about-section__body {
      font-size: 1.0625rem;
    }
  }
</style>
